# Database Rules (PostgreSQL 16)

## Database engine

This project uses **PostgreSQL 16 only**.

Do not add or reference:
- MySQL / MariaDB
- `mysql-connector-j`, `flyway-mysql`
- `jdbc:mysql` URLs or port `3306`
- MySQL-specific SQL (`AUTO_INCREMENT`, `TINYINT(1)`, `DATETIME`, `LONGTEXT`, `IFNULL`, `ON DUPLICATE KEY UPDATE`, `ENGINE=`, backticks)

Use:
- PostgreSQL JDBC driver (`org.postgresql:postgresql`)
- `flyway-database-postgresql`
- `jdbc:postgresql://...` (default port `5432`)
- Docker image `postgres:16`

## Schema management

- Flyway manages all schema changes in `backend/src/main/resources/db/migration/`.
- Hibernate uses `ddl-auto: validate` — never `update` as the primary strategy.
- Do not modify migrations that have already been applied, unless the database is confirmed resettable.

## SQL conventions (PostgreSQL)

- Primary keys: `BIGINT GENERATED BY DEFAULT AS IDENTITY`
- Booleans: `BOOLEAN` (not `TINYINT(1)`)
- Timestamps: `TIMESTAMP` (not `DATETIME`)
- Long text: `TEXT` (not `LONGTEXT`)
- Null handling: `COALESCE` (not `IFNULL`)
- Upserts: `ON CONFLICT ... DO UPDATE` (not `ON DUPLICATE KEY UPDATE`)

## Money

- Java: `BigDecimal` only — never `double` / `float`.
- Database: `NUMERIC(19, 2)` for all money columns.
- Money columns include: `price`, `amount`, `discount_amount`, `adjustment_amount`, `final_amount`, `paid_amount`, `remaining_amount`.

## Naming

- Tables and columns: `snake_case`
- Foreign keys: end with `_id`
- Migration files: `V{n}__description.sql`

## Financial correctness

Backend must enforce:
- No overpayment
- No payment for canceled or fully paid invoices
- Canceled payments excluded from `paidAmount` and revenue
- Recalculate `paidAmount`, `remainingAmount`, and invoice status after payment create/cancel
